post_cb({"bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_30166983_30167116_0": {"length": 15, "quality": 0.7894736842105263, "section_id": 6009}, "so_30166983_30167116_1": {"length": 14, "quality": 0.7, "section_id": 6010}}, "n3337": {"so_30166983_30167116_0": {"length": 15, "quality": 0.7894736842105263, "section_id": 5777}, "so_30166983_30167116_1": {"length": 14, "quality": 0.7, "section_id": 5778}}}, "30167053": {"PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>Refer to the documentation:\n<a href=\"https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/tf4dy80a.aspx\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/tf4dy80a.aspx</a></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_30166983_30167053_0\">When a postfix or prefix ++ operator is applied to a variable of type\n  bool, the variable is set to true. The postfix or prefix -- operator\n  cannot be applied to a variable of this type.</p>\n</blockquote>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2015-05-11T11:56:03.240", "Id": "30167053", "CommentCount": "8", "CreationDate": "2015-05-11T11:56:03.240", "ParentId": "30166983", "Score": "2", "OwnerUserId": "1543816"}, "30167116": {"PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>From the Standard 5.2.6.1</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_30166983_30167116_0\">The value of the operand object is modified by\n  adding 1 to it, unless the object is of type bool, in which case it is set to true. [ Note: this use is deprecated,\n  see Annex D. \u2014end note ]</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>And 5.2.6.2 emphasis mine</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_30166983_30167116_1\">The operand of postfix -- is decremented analogously to the postfix ++ operator, <strong>except that the operand\n  shall not be of type bool</strong>. [ Note: For prefix increment and decrement, see 5.3.2. \u2014end note ]</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>And Annex D</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_30166983_30167116_2\">D.1 Increment operator with bool operand [depr.incr.bool]\n  1 The use of an operand of type bool with the ++ operator is deprecated (see 5.3.2 and 5.2.6).</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>So in turn the reason you can't is because it is against the standard.</p>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2015-05-11T11:59:41.377", "Id": "30167116", "CommentCount": "0", "CreationDate": "2015-05-11T11:59:41.377", "ParentId": "30166983", "Score": "2", "OwnerUserId": "4342498"}, "30166983": {"ViewCount": "131", "Body": "<p>I was wondering why the <code>++</code> operator is defined over <code>bool</code>... however when I tried the <code>--</code>operator, it was not defined for <code>bool</code>..</p>\n<p>Can someone please explain me the reason behind that?</p>\n", "AcceptedAnswerId": "30167053", "Title": "Why \"++\" operator over bool is defined?? however \"--\" is not in C++", "CreationDate": "2015-05-11T11:52:37.830", "Id": "30166983", "CommentCount": "1", "FavoriteCount": "1", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditDate": "2015-05-11T11:56:40.400", "LastEditorUserId": "2191105", "LastActivityDate": "2015-05-11T11:59:41.377", "Tags": "<c++><operator-keyword>", "Score": "0", "OwnerUserId": "1302665", "ClosedDate": "2015-05-11T12:03:52.603", "AnswerCount": "2"}});